      <div class="msgContentFrame">Hrm, well if the game told me the recipe level I would be more than happy to NOT craft things above my level.  But seeing as how that doesnt happen *shrug* trial and error from now on.  And if it shows you what level the recipe is but not me, that aint nice :( <br /> <br />Mine looks like <br />Bone Ring <br />Ring <br /> <br />Base:Bone <br />Suits: All Classes, Slot Cost: 2 <br />Optimal Rank: 2 <br />^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ <br />Guess that doesnt refer to the optimal CRAFTING level but wearing level.  Ah well such as life. <br /> <br /> <br />You can get wind shards from mining, fishing, dodo, wharf rats, Aerulia and Puk Hatchlings (the rats are iffy, ill go butcher some now and tell ya if im right cause I need more myself).  And for general purposes I would also assume Botany can get them though I am not positive as I have no records kept nor have I done any logging/harvesting in the past 24hrs. <br /> <br />Checked another site for something totally unrelated to this and found you can make Wind Shards from Wind Crystals through alchemy with 1 fine sand and 1 wind crystal though the recipe is level 8.  You can also make crystals with shards but I have no idea what level the recipe is.  Could be wrong but who knows.   <br /> <br />The Shards -&gt; Crystal recipe is currently suspected as wrong though there being a next step up from crystals called Clusters (Or so is said) people are assuming you can go Cluster -&gt; Crystal at a later level.  Anyways, back to the rat slaughter for info xd <br /> <br />&gt;_&gt; The rats, they no like giving me wind shards. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sep 18th 2010  2:38pm by Surreal200 </span></i></div>
